  "texts": [
    "This suggests that the GPT series models' moral competence is consistent across dimensions, with a balanced moral development at each stage, exhibiting no significant shortcomings or strengths.",
    "Therefore, the improvement in moral competence from GPT-2 to ChatGPT represents a relatively comprehensive and stable process.",
    "Table 4 GPT Series human morality compliance rate (%) (invalid responses removed) GPT-2 (%) GPT-3 (%) ChatGPT (%) Full questions 59.32 83.33 96.77 Q1 group questions 50 84.38 100 Q2 group questions 70.37 82.14 93.10 Table 5 GPT series logical self-consistency rate (%) (invalid responses removed) GPT-2 (%) GPT-3 (%) ChatGPT (%) Full questions 71.43 87.50 96.72 Q1 group questions 70 80.65 93.75 Q2 group questions 75 96 100 Table 6 GPT series' rate of valid responses and providing reasons within valid responses (%) GPT-2 (%) GPT-3 (%) ChatGPT (%) Valid response rate 22.58 90.32 98.39 Rate of providing reasons within valid responses 92.86 69.64 98.36 Table 7 GPT series' numbers of reasons provided Reasons GPT-2 GPT-3 ChatGPT Rejection of violence 6 8 48 Respect/dignity 0 14 16 Fairness/justice/equality/justice 1 6 7 Order/public order/stability/harmony 0 0 3 Humanitarianism 0 0 1 Other morals 6 14 12 Rights/interests 0 1 18 Other (general/specific laws) 0 2 25 Reasoned responses 13 39 60 Unreasoned responses 1 17 1 Total valid responses 14 56 61 Average number of reasons per response 1 1.15 2.16",
    "The inclusion of Chinese LLMs for horizontal comparative analysis also provided further evidence that ChatGPT holds great potential in moral judgment.",
